name: Henry Beck
tweet: @reedteaches What I mean is, when we think of how Obama won we seem immediately think about the mechanics of his win and less the big picture approach.

name: Henry Beck
tweet: Yes, honor our coalitions+history. Not everyone will vote for us-was true for FDR, B. Clinton, Obama (and down the ballot, Booker, frankly Bernie, Shaheen, Clyburn, Sherrod and on) but all cited aim to speak to everyone and their lives + create environment where this is possible

name: Henry Beck
tweet: In a way, this was Bernie's point, Bill Clinton's skill and Obama's intent (but again, when we think of Obama's wins we seem preoccupied by "data" and technology etc.

name: Henry Beck
tweet: I believe in field, early voting + the rest but we are well advised to start with a simple goal: win from the people at large. Winning = appealing to people, as many as possible, with a message and record that matters to them. Republicans do not offer this. We have and can.

name: Henry Beck
tweet: Elections are about voters + their lives-not ego/revenge (as Trump desires) or a consumer experience (opting not to vote Hillary in 2016). However, impressiveness of Obama 2012, industry, desire for magic solutions and other factors now distract from winning strategy
